"https://news.google.com/rss/search?q=site:entertainmentnow.com","‘The Valley' Season 2 Cast Net Worths","https://entertainmentnow.com/bravo/the-valley-net-worths-jesse-jax-kristen/","Thu, 12 Jun 2025 01:26:01 GMT","

There has been speculation about whether Bravo's “The Valley” will be changing its cast for Season 3, but Season 2 focuses on the lives of Danny Booko and Nia Booko; Luke Broderick and Kristen Doute; Jason Caperna and Janet Caperna, Brittany Cartwright, Jasmine Goode, Jesse Lally, Michelle Saniei, Jax Taylor, and Zack Wickham.

Other famous faces feature on the show, with “Vanderpump Rules” stars Lala Kent, Tom Schwartz, Scheana Shay, and Brock Davies making appearances, and there are celebrities who join the cast as friends. But let's focus on the main cast, and how they make their money!

A post shared by Bravo (@bravotv)

Starring on “The Valley” can be incredibly profitable, especially if you're one of the main cast members. “Jax got paid the most for season 1 – around $30k per episode. Brittany and Kristen were just behind him, closer to 20/25k per episode. And the newer full-time cast got $5-10k per episode depending on how much they filmed,” The Sun reports an insider told them on April 14. “For season 2, every cast member's pay was significantly increased.”

Jax Taylor has worked in the entertainment industry both as an actor and a model, including an appearance in “Sharknado 4: The 4th Awakens.” He is one of the main stars of “The Valley,” and this is his second season, but he is also no stranger to reality TV and previously appeared on “Vanderpump Rules.” Celebrity Net Worth reports his net worth is estimated at $4 million.

Actress, clothing designer, and reality TV star are just a few ways to describe Kristen Doute. Her business ventures have proven to be incredibly successful because her estimated net worth is $1 million, Celebrity Net Worth reports. Doute started appearing on reality television over 10 years ago, with “Vanderpump Rules” in 2013.

Jax Taylor's ex-wife and “The Valley” co-star Brittany Cartwright's estimated net worth is $1 million, Celebrity Net Worth reports. The accumulation of her wealth stems from her appearances on reality TV series, including “Vanderpump Rules” since 2013 and “Vanderpump Rules: Jax and Brittany Take Kentucky.”

Scheana Shay has been a main star on “Vanderpump Rules” since 2013. She has also released music, worked as an actress, and featured on “The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills.” Her estimated net worth is $3 million, Celebrity Net Worth reports.

Brock Davies is married to Scheana Shay, and both stars have made appearances on “The Valley.” He is also a former professional rugby player and personal trainer, and is active on social media. Reality Tea reports that he has an estimated net worth of $3 million.

Michelle Saniei has accumulated her wealth through her work in luxury real estate and her appearances on reality TV. However, her estimated net worth is unclear. Jesse Lally's net worth is also unclear and does not appear to have been calculated by any reputable sources online. However, Saniei has made claims that her ex is “broke” during “The Valley” Season 2, Episode 3, Bravo TV reports.

A post shared by Jax (@mrjaxtaylor)

There has been speculation about the cast for “The Valley” Season 3 because of the drama that the bitter splits between cast members have created. This includes the end of Jesse Lally and Michelle Saniei's relationship, as well as the contentious split between Jax Taylor and Brittany Cartwright.

“The reason they're casting, is because they don't want the show to end up like ‘Vanderpump Rules,' where you have a cast that won't film with each other,” an insider said, OK! Magazine reports. “Right now you have Jax Taylor and Brittany Cartwright, who are going through a bitter divorce, and you have Jesse Lally and Michelle Lally, who are also going through a brutal split. It wouldn't make sense for any of these estranged couples to go on trips together or spend time together going forward.”

What this means for their future net worths and who will remain on the show, and who could potentially be replaced, is currently unclear.

